  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    NEFFICS Service Modelling Editor: AT-ONE modelling&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The NEFFICS Service Modelling Editor has been designed to support the modelling of the five AT-ONE lenses as explained&#xD;
    in the following subsections. The tool is intended to be used by the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.innovation.service_innovation.base-sintef/roles/core_team_4EA7A2C8.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_0OMkIKF0EeCuNfGI7-CeEA&quot;>Core team&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;as a means of documenting, analysing and presenting their&#xD;
    results.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Cloud-based installation (URL)&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;http://tomcat.thingml.org/backend/poem/repository&quot;>&lt;u>&lt;font&#xD;
        color=&quot;#0066cc&quot;>http://tomcat.thingml.org/backend/poem/repository&lt;/font>&lt;/u>&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Actors&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Actors (networks) are modelled and visualized as Service Architectures. We use a hybrid notation:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Participants (from Value Network) represent the&amp;nbsp;actors in the network.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Conversation (from BPMN 2.0) which groups a set of Flows.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/atone_actors.png&quot; width=&quot;468&quot; height=&quot;280&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Touchpoints&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Touchpoints are modelled and visualized in Service Journey Maps with links to the Actors. A Service Journey&#xD;
    represents&amp;nbsp;a chronological mapping (from the customer point of view) of a service encounter.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Model as &quot;Stages&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Attach touchpoints to the different stages&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Library of different types of touchpoints to select from.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/atone_touchpoints.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;470&quot; />&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Offerings&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Offerings are modelled and visualized as Service Contracts. A Service Contract is a detailing of the conversation.&#xD;
    Conversation is the grouping of flows (messages). Service Contract defines the interfaces on both side (structure) and&#xD;
    the protocol (behaviour) for how to use these interfaces.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/atone_offerings.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;396&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Needs&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Needs modelling is not implemented yet, but the tool will be extended with BMM goals modelling. The&amp;nbsp;idea is to use&#xD;
    a very small subset of BMM (Business Motivation Model) standard allowing to model goals and objectives:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Goal:&lt;/strong> A statement about a state or condition of the enterprise to be brought about or sustained&#xD;
        through appropriate Means (i.e., Offerings expressed as Service Contracts).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Objective:&lt;/strong> An Objective is a statement of an attainable, time-targeted, and measurable target that&#xD;
        the enterprise seeks to meet in order to achieve its Goals.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    An example of Goals and Objectives diagram is shown below (Xactium tool, not Oryx-based).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;resources/atone_needs.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;382&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Experiences&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Experiences can be modelled as different emotional icons and comparing different service journeys. The idea is to&#xD;
    extend the Service Journey Map. Each user/customer capture experiences (emotional icons) related to each touchpoints&#xD;
    and deviations in the ideal/expected journey (seen from a Service Provider side).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;resources/atone_experiences.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;396&quot; /></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
